Boil a large #pot of @salt{} water for the @orzo{170%grams}.

When boiling, add the orzo to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve and pop back
in the pot.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, tear the @smoked salmon{100%grams} into large pieces.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw salmon.

Chop the @tomato{2} into 2cm cubes.

Mix @sun dried tomato paste{1%sachet}, half the @italian herbs{½%sachet} and 
@mayo{2%sachets} in a large #bowl. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and 
@pepper{to taste}.

Add the orzo, @salad leaves{40%grams} and tomatoes to the bowl. Toss together to
coat.

Arrange orzo salad in deep plates or #bowls.

Top with smoked salmon and serve.